    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen call `vim.notify('123', vim.log.levels.ERROR)` **before** `vim.opt.cmdheight = 2`, it prints only `Error detected while processing`, but no \"123\" printed.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"809\" alt=\"CleanShot 2023-03-13 at 01 45 37@2x\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1998490/224562669-10d63d7c-bce2-4a44-b6e6-addad8339fb4.png\">\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nNote: When call `vim.notify` **after** `cmdheight=2`, it works as expected.\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.opt.cmdheight = 2\r\nvim.notify('123', vim.log.levels.ERROR)\r\n```\r\n\r\n<img width=\"868\" alt=\"CleanShot 2023-03-13 at 01 47 00@2x\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1998490/224562761-60b1b3bf-e2c9-41ce-a0b6-c22165b6f936.png\">\r\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create a `minimal.lua` file.\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.notify('123', vim.log.levels.ERROR)\r\nvim.opt.cmdheight = 2\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. `nvim --clean -u ./minimal.lua`. You will see the error message that missing \"123\".\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nPrint the error message includes \"123\".\r\n\r\n<img width=\"868\" alt=\"CleanShot 2023-03-13 at 01 47 00@2x\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1998490/224562728-a98e1f68-93bb-4c36-91a2-9ab52155329d.png\">\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.8.3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno test\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nMacOS 12.2\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niTerm2 3.5.0beta10\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
